column2: Q1. For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
column4: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
column6: SELECT t.sid, t.version FROM ( SELECT bm.sid, bm.version, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY bm.sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rn FROM BaseModel bm GROUP BY bm.sid, bm.version) t WHERE t.rn = 1;

column2: Q1. For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
column4: Achieve this NL2SQL task from the given natural language query and attached schema: What are the most frequently used versions among all base models for each internet service sid? If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them. The attached zip is the schema of the database.
column6: WITH version_counts AS (SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS freq FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version), ranked AS (SELECT sid, version, freq, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY freq DESC) AS rn FROM version_counts) SELECT sid, version FROM ranked WHERE rn = 1;

column2: Q2. Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
column4: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
column6: SELECT u.sid FROM utilizes u JOIN base_models b ON u.bid = b.bid WHERE b.creator = 'user_iuwrh' GROUP BY u.sid HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT u.bid) = (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b2.bid) FROM base_models b2 WHERE b2.creator = 'user_iuwrh');

column2: Q2. Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
column4: Achieve this NL2SQL task from the given natural language query and attached schema: What are the sid's utilized in every base model built by user_iuwrh? The attached zip is the schema of the database.
column6: SELECT ms.sid FROM ModelServices AS ms JOIN BaseModel AS bm ON ms.bmid = bm.bmid JOIN User AS u ON bm.creator_uid = u.uid WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh' GROUP BY ms.sid HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ms.bmid) = ( SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT bm2.bmid) FROM BaseModel AS bm2 JOIN User AS u2 ON bm2.creator_uid = u2.uid WHERE u2.username = 'user_iuwrh' );

column2: Q3. Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
column4: Translate this query using NL2SQL: What are the mid's that do not appear in model configurations given this schema: "BaseModel": {"bmid": "INT","creator_uid": "INT","description": "TEXT"},"CustomizedModel": {"bmid": "INT","mid": "INT"},"Configuration": {"cid": "INT","client_uid": "INT","content": "TEXT","labels": "TEXT"},"ModelConfigurations": {"bmid": "INT","mid": "INT","cid": "INT","duration": "INT"}
column6: SELECT DISTINCT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel cm WHERE cm.mid NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT mc.mid FROM ModelConfigurations mc);

column2: Q3. Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
column4: Achieve this NL2SQL task from the given natural language query and attached schema: Which customized model mid's do not appear in model configurations? The attached zip file is the schema of the database.
column6: SELECT DISTINCT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel AS cm LEFT JOIN ModelConfigurations AS mc ON cm.mid = mc.mid WHERE mc.mid IS NULL;

column2: Q3. Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
column4: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
column6: SELECT m.mid FROM customized_models AS m WHERE m.mid NOT IN (SELECT mc.mid FROM model_configurations AS mc);
